Bybit to list MV tokens after Launchpool program!! Full schedule released here.

January 13, 2022

The GensoKishi Online Project is pleased to announce that Bybit, the leading global Cryptocurrency exchange has decided to partner with us and list our Metaverse (MV) token.

How big is Bybit?

ByBit is one of the biggest crypto exchanges in the world and is trusted by traders around the world. They are known for their interactive UI and is one of the most popular exchanges among traders.

Metaverse (MV) will be listed on ByBit after the Launchpool.

Metaverse (MV) will be launched on Bybit’s launchpool before it’s listing.

Jan. 19,2022 Bybit launchpool
Jan. 27,2022 Bybit Listing

The Bybit Launchpool allows you to stake and earn tokens for free. The tokens you’ve staked can be unstaked anytime. 

If you wish to participate, you need to open an account with Bybit and complete the KYC Level 1, so you need to proceed as soon as possible. Please be aware of this.

The detailed rules for participation will be announced on the Bybit blog, so please wait for further information.

Coordination of various schedules

As a result, there will be some schedule changes.
We apologize to those who have already purchased tokens on Whitelist and to those who have been waiting for the MV token sale.

Jan 17 → Changed to February 7
　1st NFT Skin Auction

Jan 18 12:00 pm UTC – 17:00 pm UTC
　TRUSTPAD IDO

Jan 19 12:00 pm UTC – Jan 26 11:59 am UTC
　Bybit Launch Pad

Jan 20 → Changed to Jan 27
　MV distribution to Whitelist MV buyers

January 27 10:00 am UTC
　Bybit listing

Jan 20→ Changed to Jan 31
　Uniswap and QuickSwap listing

We are very sorry for the repeated schedule adjustments, but thanks to those who read this announcement and those who have been warmly watching the project’s progress in various communities, we have been able to be listed on the industry’s leading exchange Bybit, and we would like to continue developing a project that will please everyone.

Restricted countries: United States of America,China,Hong Kong, and all sanctioned OFAC countries(DR Congo,Iran,Myanmar,Sudan,Iraq,Ivory Coast,North Korea,Syria,Zimbabwe,Cuba,Balarus,Liberia)
